    <!-- =========================================================== -->
    <section class="api-section" id="wsq-schedule">
        <header>
            <h2>WSQ Schedule API</h2>
            <span class="api-pill method-get">GET</span>
            <span class="api-pill scope-public">Public · API-key gated</span>
        </header>

        <p>Read-only endpoint listing every WSQ course (<code>TGS-</code> SKU prefix) enabled in the Singapore store, with its scheduled class dates. Consumed by the external TMS to keep its course catalog in sync.</p>

        <h3>Endpoint</h3>
        <pre class="url-block">GET <?php echo $this->htmlEscape($prodBaseUrl); ?>/courses/api_schedule</pre>
        <p style="color:#9aa0a6;font-size:12px;margin-top:-8px;">Localhost equivalent: <code><?php echo $this->htmlEscape($localBaseUrl); ?>/courses/api_schedule</code></p>

        <h3>Authentication</h3>
        <p>Send the shared secret on every request as an HTTP header:</p>
        <pre>X-API-Key: &lt;your key&gt;</pre>

        <p><strong>Current key</strong> <span style="color:#9aa0a6;">— rotate via System → Configuration → MMD → Provider Manager → WSQ Schedule API Key. Setting it blank disables the endpoint (503).</span></p>
        <div class="key-box">
            <code id="apikey-value" data-revealed="0" data-full="<?php echo $this->htmlEscape($apiKey); ?>"><?php echo $this->htmlEscape($apiKeyMasked); ?></code>
            <button type="button" class="reveal-toggle" onclick="apiDocsToggleKey()">Reveal</button>
            <button type="button" onclick="apiDocsCopyKey()">Copy</button>
        </div>

        <h3>Status codes</h3>
        <table class="api-table">
            <thead><tr><th style="width:90px;">Status</th><th>Meaning</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr class="status-row"><td><code>200</code></td><td>Authenticated; payload returned</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>401</code></td><td>Missing or wrong <code>X-API-Key</code> → <code>{"error":"unauthorized"}</code></td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>500</code></td><td>Server error → <code>{"error":"internal_error"}</code>. Check <code>var/log/exception.log</code> on the LMS host.</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>503</code></td><td>Endpoint disabled (server-side key is blank) → <code>{"error":"api_disabled"}</code></td></tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>

        <h3>Scope</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Enabled products only</strong> (<code>status = 1</code>) — disabled / discontinued courses are excluded.</li>
            <li>SKU starts with <code>TGS-</code> (the SkillsFuture course reference — defines "WSQ" per the LMS data model).</li>
            <li>Singapore store view only (<code>store_id = 1</code>); titles and option labels are returned in the SG storefront's text.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Response</h3>
        <p><code>Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8</code> · <code>Cache-Control: no-store</code> (always fresh; do not edge-cache).</p>

        <p><strong>Top-level shape</strong></p>
        <pre>{
  "generated_at": "2026-05-31T05:45:28+00:00",
  "store": "singapore",
  "count": 299,
  "courses": [ ... ]
}</pre>
        <table class="api-table">
            <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr><td><code>generated_at</code></td><td>string (ISO 8601, UTC)</td><td>Server-side timestamp at response build</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>store</code></td><td>string</td><td>Always <code>"singapore"</code> in v1 (WSQ is SG-only)</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>count</code></td><td>integer</td><td>Number of courses in <code>courses[]</code></td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>courses</code></td><td>array</td><td>List of course objects (see below)</td></tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>

        <p><strong>Course object</strong></p>
        <pre>{
  "course_code": "TGS-2023021752",
  "course_title": "WSQ - Mastering The Art of Conflict Resolution ...",
  "schedules": [ ... ]
}</pre>
        <table class="api-table">
            <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr><td><code>course_code</code></td><td>string</td><td><strong>The SKU and the official SkillsFuture course reference.</strong> Always <code>TGS-</code> prefix. Stable primary key — TMS should join on this.</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>course_title</code></td><td>string</td><td>Course name as shown in the SG storefront.</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>schedules</code></td><td>array</td><td>May be empty (course exists but has no scheduled dates).</td></tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>

        <p><strong>Schedule object</strong></p>
        <pre>{
  "raw": "29 Jun - 3 Jul 2026 (Mon-Fri)",
  "course_start_date": "2026-06-29",
  "course_end_date": "2026-07-03"
}</pre>
        <table class="api-table">
            <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr><td><code>raw</code></td><td>string</td><td>The exact label shown to learners on the storefront's "Course Date" dropdown. <strong>Always present.</strong></td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>course_start_date</code></td><td>string <code>YYYY-MM-DD</code> or <code>null</code></td><td>First class day. <code>null</code> only when the raw label is in an unsupported format (~0.25% of rows).</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>course_end_date</code></td><td>string <code>YYYY-MM-DD</code> or <code>null</code></td><td>Last class day. Same nullability as start. For a same-day course, start == end.</td></tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>

        <div class="note">
            <strong>Null handling:</strong> if <code>course_start_date</code> is <code>null</code>, fall back to displaying / parsing <code>raw</code>. Do not drop the row — these are real, live class offerings the parser couldn't normalise (typically multi-segment cross-month labels like <code>"23/24/31 May /06/07 Jun 2026"</code>).
        </div>

        <h3>Supported label formats</h3>
        <table class="api-table">
            <thead><tr><th>Pattern</th><th>Example</th><th>Parsed output</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr><td>Single day</td><td><code>20 May 2026</code></td><td>start = end = <code>2026-05-20</code></td></tr>
                <tr><td>Slash, same-month</td><td><code>25/26 May 2026 (Mon/Tue)</code></td><td><code>2026-05-25</code> → <code>2026-05-26</code></td></tr>
                <tr><td>Multi-day slash same-month</td><td><code>7/8/10 Mar 2016</code></td><td>First to last day</td></tr>
                <tr><td>Hyphen range same-month</td><td><code>15-18 Jul 2026</code></td><td><code>2026-07-15</code> → <code>2026-07-18</code></td></tr>
                <tr><td>Cross-month slash</td><td><code>30 Nov / 1 Dec 2023</code></td><td><code>2023-11-30</code> → <code>2023-12-01</code></td></tr>
                <tr><td>Cross-month slash compact</td><td><code>30/1 June/July 2018</code></td><td><code>2018-06-30</code> → <code>2018-07-01</code></td></tr>
                <tr><td>Cross-month hyphen</td><td><code>29 Jun - 3 Jul 2026</code></td><td><code>2026-06-29</code> → <code>2026-07-03</code></td></tr>
                <tr><td>Dot / ampersand separators</td><td><code>21.22 Feb 2019</code>, <code>4 &amp; 11 July 2015</code></td><td>First to last day</td></tr>
                <tr><td>ISO</td><td><code>2026-05-20</code></td><td>Pass-through</td></tr>
                <tr><td>With bracket noise</td><td><code>08 Nov 2021 (Mon) [Zoom only]</code></td><td>Annotations stripped before parsing</td></tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>

        <h3>Caching &amp; polling</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Server sends <code>Cache-Control: no-store</code>. Each call recomputes from the live DB.</li>
            <li>Payload is ~440 KB for the current catalog (299 courses, ~4,800 schedule rows). Poll every 5–15 minutes.</li>
            <li>No webhook in v1 — TMS polls. The payload changes only when admin staff edit course schedules.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Stability &amp; versioning</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><code>course_code</code> is the join key. It is permanent; never reused for a different course.</li>
            <li>Field names are stable. Future additive fields (e.g. <code>trainer_name</code>, <code>course_mode</code>) will be added without breaking existing consumers — <strong>TMS must ignore unknown fields</strong>.</li>
            <li>Incompatible changes would land at <code>/courses/api_schedule/v2</code>; v1 stays for a deprecation window.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Smoke test</h3>
        <pre>curl -sS \
  -H "X-API-Key: <span style="color:#f3c97a;">&lt;your key&gt;</span>" \
  <?php echo $this->htmlEscape($prodBaseUrl); ?>/courses/api_schedule \
  | jq '{count, sample: .courses[0]}'</pre>

        <p><strong>Expected output</strong></p>
        <pre>{
  "count": 299,
  "sample": {
    "course_code": "TGS-2023021752",
    "course_title": "WSQ - Mastering The Art of Conflict Resolution ...",
    "schedules": [
      {
        "raw": "25/26 May 2026 (Mon/Tue)",
        "course_start_date": "2026-05-25",
        "course_end_date": "2026-05-26"
      }
    ]
  }
}</pre>

        <div class="warn">
            <strong>Rotation:</strong> when rotating the API key, update the TMS configuration before rotating here — otherwise the TMS will start receiving 401s. There is no grace period and no key history.
        </div>
    </section>

